 come along it's possible that we'd have a base on the Moon. To get back on topic, I think the Americans would have just abandoned sending anyone anywhere or they would have gone the Soviet route of designing a permanent lunar base.      <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 12/16/02 11:58:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1681<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/22/02 1:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1> That Space Shuttle has been a waste... the Russians must have thought we knew something they didn't and built a copy based on the false assumption that it was the best method for access to LEO.  Why would the capitalist pigs build it if it wasn't profitable?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 576<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/22/02 3:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    It wouldn't surprise me if somewhere down the road we learn that the real reason for building the space shuttle was simply to make the Soviets bankrupt themselves trying to copy it.  It would have been awesome though if the Soviets did go ahead with building a moon base.  After the USSR went belly up in the early 90s the moon base probably could have been turned into an international project since the Russians would already have the technology to get there and back.  It would just be a matter of expansion and it would have been a hell of a lot more exciting than that damned International Budget Buster.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 12/22/02 3:56:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1692<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/24/02 2:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A Soviet moonbase would have been pretty cool!  It's too bad the<br>
'Space Race' ended... but I guess that is the cost of the end of<br>
the Cold War.<br>
<br>
If the Soviets had built a moonbase, would the US build one too?  <br>
Probably.  Maybe an Orion type NPR would have been more probable<br>
had the US lost the race to the moon.  One battle lost, but not<br>
the war!  Mars would be the next battle ground in the Space Race. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 587<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 7:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1> Yeah I bet we'd be a lot further in space right now if we had stuck with rockets like the Saturn V and tried to keep humiliating the Soviets by getting further and further out there.  I think it's quite possible that we could have had a base on Mars by now if we didn't make absolutely everything revolve around the space shuttle which is very limited in what it can do and very expensive.  Getting rid of heavy lift rockets like the Saturn V was the absolute dumbest mistake the USA made concerning space.  We should have kept working on bigger, better, and cheaper boosters like the Sea Dragon.  Everytime I see the space shuttle I want to puke all over it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2772<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/30/02 12:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1> If the Russians had reached the Moon first the the US would have built nuclear space rockets for reaching Mars. It would have been Sputnik all over again. A frightened public would look from the moon to the government and expect an answer. The Russians have put up the first Satellite, the first man in space and the first man on the moon. All that is left is Mars. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lgeorgedaniels>LGeorgeDaniels</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/31/02 1:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if the Russians won the moon race?</span><hr size=1>  Dear All --<br>
<br>
This subject is near and dear to my heart.<br>
<br>
(This will expose my age ... ) A few days before Apollo 11 lifted off for the Moon, the Soviets launched Luna 15, and in my fevered 12 year-old imagination I wondered if &quot;they were going to try to beat us&quot; with some last ditch attempt. Three years later, in junior high I wrote this into a short story which I have long since lost.<br>
<br>
A close friend from my junior high days, David S. Michaels, managed to visit the Sotheby's auction of Soviet Space hardware (meeting no less than Alexi Leonov!) and my short story sprang to mind. Seized by dramatic possibilities, and the recent success of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Apollo 13</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he contacted me and we went through a couple of versions and wound up with what we feel is a very good novel, entitled <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Red Moon</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. His agent basically published it as a print-on-demand item as a marketing ploy, but unfortunately it did not get a big publishing contract.<br>
<br>
