I understand the reference to May 1, but actually I would think this would be June 6 or 7, 1969.  I'm not clear if there was a launch window on that date, but the Soviets attempted a launch of their Saturn V class booster the N1 on June 3.  There was speculation for years this may have been a lunar attempt.  More about the N1 (with a bunch of photos) at <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Encyclopedia Astronautica</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br>
