In <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Red Moon</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the lander was the spherical cabin from the LK you have pictured here, and the landing stage from the Lavochkin Luna probes (the actual Luna 15 &amp; 16 sample return probes, and the stage that landed the Lunakhods).  We left the docking apparatus off, following Mark Wade's suggestion.<br>
<br>
